quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  12,103,"And most of mankind will not believe even if you desire it eagerly."
  12,104,"And no reward you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) ask of them (those who deny your Prophethood) for it; it (the Qur’ân) is no less than a Reminder and an advice unto the ‘Âlamîn (men and jinn)."
  12,105,"And how many a sign in the heavens and the earth they pass by, while they are averse therefrom."
  14,49,"And you will see the Mujrimûn (criminals, disbelievers in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism, polytheists) that Day Muqarranûn{1} (bound together) in fetters.",1:[{14:49} Muqarranûn in fetters mean with their hands and feet tied to their necks with chains.]
  14,50,"Their garments will be of pitch, and fire will cover their faces."
  14,51,"That Allâh may requite each person according to what he has earned. Truly, Allâh is Swift at reckoning."
  15,22,"And We send the winds fertilizing (to fill heavily the clouds with water), then cause the water (rain) to descend from the sky, and We give it to you to drink, and it is not you who are the owners of its stores [i.e. to give water to whom you like or to withhold it from whom you like]."
  15,23,"And certainly We! We it is Who give life, and cause death,{1} and We are the Inheritors.",1:[{15:23} Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said: "When a person is dead, his deeds cease (are stopped) except three:]
  15,24,"And indeed, We know the first generations of you who had passed away, and indeed, We know the present generations of you (mankind), and also those who will come afterwards."
  16,1,"The Event (the Hour or the punishment of disbelievers and polytheists or the Islâmic laws or commandments) ordained by Allâh will come to pass, so seek not to hasten it. Glorified and Exalted be He above all that they associate as partners with Him."
  16,2,"He sends down the angels with the Rûh (revelation) of His Command to whom of His slaves He wills (saying): "
  16,3,"He has created the heavens and the earth with truth. High is He, Exalted above all that they associate as partners with Him."